Aviva May Name Barclays’ Broadbent as Chairman, FT Reports

-- B y   B r i a n   S w i n t
-- 
2011-03-26T07:54:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-26/aviva-may-name-barclay-s-broadbent-as-chairman-ft-reports.html
Richard Broadbent, deputy chairman
of  Barclays Plc (BARC) , is the leading candidate to become chairman of
 Aviva Plc (AV/) , the Financial Times reported, citing unidentified
people with knowledge of the matter.  Aviva Chairman Colin Sharman is due to retire in 2013 and
Broadbent hasn’t yet agreed to take the job, the FT said.  Aviva, the U.K.’s second-biggest insurer by market value,
and Broadbent declined to comment, the FT said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
